ST. PETERSBURG — The Black Art & Film Festival is back in the Sunshine City for its fourth year. The annual five-day festival returned Wednesday with a cocktail social at Urban Drinkery. Events continue through Sunday. Screenings take place at the Green Light Cinema and Sundial AMC Theater in downtown St. Petersburg, featuring documentaries and feature-length films to music videos and shorts. The works of several Tampa Bay area artists will be included. In addition to film screenings, the festival also features professional workshops and networking events led by industry professionals. “Come be a part of an experience designed to ignite your creative engine and kick into high gear the process of you moving from an idea that’s stuck in your head to actually experiencing the reality of it being something tangibly real,” reads the festival website. “BAFF is about helping artist and filmmakers push the needle forward and helping those who dare to dream the ability to get one step closer to seeing their dreams become a living reality.” Tickets range from $5 to $15 per event. For a schedule and tickets, visit blackartandfilmfestival.com.